    tool_output=ToolOutput(
        output='# SpaceX S-1 Disclosure: Common-Control Accounting, Mergers, Recast Financials, and Segment Reporting\n\n## 1. Common-Control Accounting\n\nThe S-1 discloses that both the **xAI Merger** and the **X Merger** were accounted for as **reorganizations of entities under common control**. The basis for this treatment is that Elon Musk held a **controlling financial interest** in SpaceX, xAI, and X through his **majority voting interest** in each entity during all periods presented in the consolidated financial statements.\n\nKey accounting consequences of this common-control treatment include:\n\n- **Retrospective combination at historical carrying amounts**: The consolidated financial statements reflect the combination of the net assets of SpaceX, xAI, and X at their **historical carrying amounts** for all periods presented — not at fair value.\n- **No new goodwill or intangible assets**: Because the transactions were common-control reorganizations, **no new goodwill or other intangible assets** were recorded.\n- **Elimination of intercompany transactions**: All historical related-party transactions between SpaceX, xAI, and X have been **eliminated in consolidation**.\n- **Equity continuation**: The capital stock and shareholders\' equity for all periods presented reflects a **continuation of the historical SpaceX capital stock and shareholders\' equity**, combined with the historical capital stock and shareholders\' equity of X and xAI, **as adjusted by the respective exchange ratios** used to effect the Mergers.\n- **Change in reporting entity**: The filing explicitly states that this presentation **constitutes a change in reporting entity**.\n\n## 2. The xAI Merger\n\n- **Effective date**: February 2, 2026 (the "xAI Merger Date").\n- **Structure**: SpaceX acquired X.AI Holdings Corp. ("xAI"), pursuant to which xAI became a **wholly-owned subsidiary** of SpaceX.\n- **Form of consideration**: The merger was effected through a **share exchange**.\n- **Preferred stock conversion**: All of xAI\'s **redeemable convertible preferred stock** was converted to SpaceX common stock as part of the xAI Merger. Former xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock shareholders received applicable shares of SpaceX Common Stock (specifically SpaceX Class B Common Stock, on a pre-2026 Stock Split basis, rounded up for fractional shares). For xAI Series A Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, eligible service providers could elect to receive **$75.46 per share** (on a pre-2026 Stock Split basis) in cash.\n- **Cancellation of intercompany holdings**: Any shares of xAI Common Stock or Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock previously held by SpaceX were **canceled and retired** and received no consideration.\n\n### Accounting Treatment of xAI Preferred Stock\n\nA nuanced point is disclosed: although xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock converted into SpaceX Common Stock upon the xAI Merger closing, the **xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock balances are presented as Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock** in the consolidated financial statements for **all periods presented prior to the xAI Merger Date**. The rationale is that:\n\n- The xAI preferred stock was **legally outstanding** during all historical periods prior to the xAI Merger.\n- It represented a **separate equity class of a legally distinct predecessor entity**.\n- Therefore, the conversion is recognized **only in the period in which the exchange actually occurs** (Q1 2026), and **not retrospectively**.\n- The historical consolidated balance sheets and statements of redeemable convertible preferred stock and shareholders\' equity reflect the xAI preferred stock as outstanding **consistent with its legal form and rights** during those periods and are **not recast on an as-converted basis**.\n- The impact of the conversion is presented **prospectively** in the period of the merger (Q1 2026).\n\n## 3. The X Merger (X Holdings into xAI)\n\n- **Effective date**: March 28, 2025.\n- **Structure**: xAI completed its acquisition of **X Holdings Corp. ("X")** and **X.AI Corp.**, in which both became **wholly-owned subsidiaries of xAI**.\n- **Form of consideration**: Effected through a **share exchange**.\n- **Historical context**: X.AI Corp. began operations in **March 2023**. Twitter, Inc. was acquired by Elon Musk in **October 2022**.\n\n### Exchange Ratios\n\nThe filing discloses specific conversion ratios upon the effective date of the X Merger:\n\n| Security Converted | Conversion Ratio | Into |\n|---|---|---|\n| Each class of **X Holdings Corp. Common Stock** ("X Common Stock") | **2.776** shares (rounded down to nearest whole share) | xAI Common Stock of the same class |\n| Each class of **X.AI Corp. Common Stock** | **1.000** share | xAI Common Stock of the same class |\n| Each series of **X.AI Corp. Preferred Stock** (other than shares held by X or its subsidiaries) | **1.000** share | xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock |\n\n## 4. Recast Financial Statements and Presentation of Historical Periods\n\n### Retrospective Recasting\n\nThe consolidated financial statements of SpaceX have been **retrospectively recast for all periods presented** to include:\n\n1. **(i)** The historical results of **X.AI Holdings Corp.** (acquired by SpaceX effective February 2, 2026) and **X Holdings Corp.** (acquired by xAI effective March 28, 2025), because these transactions were between entities under common control; and\n2. **(ii)** A **five-for-one stock split** of the Company\'s Class A, Class B, and Class C Common Stock, effective May 4, 2026 (the "2026 Stock Split").\n\n### Retroactive Share Adjustments\n\n- All share and per share information in the prospectus has been **retroactively adjusted** to reflect the 2026 Stock Split for all periods presented.\n- The conversion rate of SpaceX Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock was **proportionately adjusted** to factor in the 2026 Stock Split.\n- As a result of the Mergers, all shares of historical X, X.AI Corp., and xAI Common Stock are **presented in the historical financial statements as if they had been converted into SpaceX Common Stock** at the applicable exchange rate for all periods presented through the date of the xAI Merger.\n- All shares of historical X, X.AI Corp., and xAI Common Stock are **included in the share counts for SpaceX Common Stock**.\n- X.AI Corp. and xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock are presented in the consolidated financial statements at **historical values with an adjustment to the conversion rate** at the applicable exchange ratio per the xAI Merger.\n\n### Cautionary Language on Historical Data\n\nThe filing cautions that:\n\n> "The summary historical consolidated financial and operating data presented below is **not indicative of the results to be expected for any future period**, and the results for any interim period are not necessarily indicative of the results to be expected for the full fiscal period."\n\nReaders are directed to the **Management\'s Discussion and Analysis** section and the consolidated financial statements and related notes for full context.\n\n## 5. Standalone Financial Statements — Omission Justified\n\nThe S-1 explicitly states that **separate financial statements of xAI and X are not provided**. The justification is straightforward:\n\n> "As the consolidated financial statements already reflect the reorganization of entities under common control for all periods presented, separate financial statements of xAI and X are not provided."\n\nBecause the retrospective combination has already been reflected for all periods, standalone financials would be redundant.\n\n## 6. Segment Reporting\n\n### Post-Merger Segment Realignment\n\nFollowing the Mergers, SpaceX evaluated how to view and measure performance of the combined company and the potential realignment of each individual entity\'s historical segment structure. Following this evaluation, the Company determined that **effective in Q1 2026**, the CEO (as the **Chief Operating Decision Maker, or "CODM"**) organizes the Company, manages resource allocations, and measures performance among **three operating and reportable segments**:\n\n| Segment | Description |\n|---|---|\n| **Space** | Designs, manufactures, and launches reusable rockets to provide high cadence, reliable, and affordable access to space at unprecedented scale. Includes Falcon launch vehicles, Dragon spacecraft, and the in-development Starship system. |\n| **Connectivity** | Operates a worldwide high-speed, low-latency broadband network powered by over 9,600 Starlink broadband and mobile satellites in Low-Earth Orbit, delivering connectivity to millions of consumer, enterprise, and government customers across 164 countries, territories, and other markets. Includes Starlink Mobile (satellite-to-mobile texting and voice services). |\n| **AI** | Operates a vertically integrated AI platform spanning: (a) the frontier LLM **Grok**, (b) AI solutions for consumer and enterprise customers, (c) **X** — a real-time information, entertainment, and free speech platform — and (d) AI computational infrastructure. |\n\n### CODM Performance Measurement\n\n- The CODM assesses performance and allocates resources to operating segments based on **segment income (loss) from operations**, by comparing actual income (loss) from operations to **historical results and previously forecasted financial information**.\n- The CODM does **not** evaluate operating and reportable segments using [the text is truncated, but the implication is that segments are not evaluated on a standalone or consolidated basis other than through segment income from operations].\n- **Prior period presentations for segments conform to the current segment reporting structure**, meaning historical segment data has been recast to align with the new three-segment structure.\n\n### Segment Data Tables\n\nThe filing indicates that tables presenting **revenues, significant segment expenses, and income (loss) from operations** by reportable segment are included, though the specific numerical data is not fully captured in the provided chunks.\n\n## 7. Pro Forma Information\n\nThe capitalization table in the filing presents data under three columns as of **March 31, 2026**:\n\n| Item | Actual | Pro Forma | Pro Forma as Adjusted |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Cash and cash equivalents | $15,852M | $15,852M | $ [not shown] |\n| SpaceX Bridge Loan | $20,000M | $20,000M | — |\n| X 2027 and X 2030 Notes | $27M | $27M | — |\n| Other Financings | $9,105M | $9,105M | — |\n| Total long-term debt | $29,111M | $29,111M | — |\n| Redeemable convertible preferred stock | $7,049M (189,155,861 shares issued; 134,451,267 outstanding) | $— (no shares authorized, issued, or outstanding) | $— |\n| Class A common stock — shares issued and outstanding | 2,964,501,353 issued; 2,882,444,444 outstanding | 6,824,581,339 issued and outstanding (36,132,150,000 authorized) | [shares issued and outstanding not fully shown] |\n\nThe **Pro Forma** column reflects the conversion of all redeemable convertible preferred stock into common stock (eliminating the $7,049M preferred stock balance) and the corresponding increase in Class A common shares from approximately 2.88 billion to approximately 6.82 billion. The **Pro Forma as Adjusted** column further reflects the shares offered in the IPO (the specific share counts and cash figures for this column are truncated in the provided text). Cash and debt figures remain unchanged between Actual and Pro Forma, confirming that the mergers were stock-for-stock transactions with no cash consideration at the SpaceX level.\n\n## 8. Additional Context\n\n### Exhibit Index — Merger Agreement\n\nThe Exhibit Index (Item 16) lists **Exhibit 2.1** as the **Agreement and Plan of Merger and Reorganization**, by and among Space Exploration Technologies Corp., X.AI Holdings Corp., K2 Merger Sub Inc., and K2 Merger Sub 2 LLC, dated **January 31, 2026** — just two days before the February 2, 2026 xAI Merger Date.\n\n### Audited Financial Statements\n\nThe filing includes audited consolidated financial statements covering:\n\n- **Consolidated Balance Sheets** as of December 31, 2025 and 2024\n- **Consolidated Statements of Operations** for the years ended December 31, 2025, 2024, and 2023\n- **Consolidated Statements of Comprehensive Income (Loss)** for the same periods\n- **Consolidated Statements of Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock and Shareholders\' Equity** for the same periods\n- **Consolidated Statements of Cash Flows** for the same periods\n\nAll of these financial statements have been retrospectively recast to reflect the common-control combinations and the 2026 Stock Split.\n\n### Recent Financial Performance\n\nThe filing notes that for the **three months ended March 31, 2026**, SpaceX generated **$4,694 million** in revenue on a consolidated basis.\n\n---\n\n**In summary**, the SpaceX S-1 presents a comprehensively recast set of financial statements that retrospectively combine SpaceX, xAI, and X at historical carrying amounts under common-control accounting, with no goodwill recognition, elimination of intercompany transactions, and retroactive adjustment of all share counts for both the merger exchange ratios and the 2026 five-for-one stock split. The only exception to retrospective treatment is the xAI Redeemable Convertible Preferred Stock, which is presented in its historical legal form until the Q1 2026 merger date. Standalone financial statements for xAI and X are omitted as unnecessary. The post-merger company reports under three segments — Space, Connectivity, and AI — with prior periods conformed to this structure, and the CODM evaluates segment performance based on segment income (loss) from operations.',
        error=None,
