| $0.5M (2024), $4M (2025) |\n\n## 3. Why No Goodwill Was Recorded\n\nThe S-1 **states the conclusion but does not provide an extended explanatory rationale**. The relevant passage reads:\n\n> "The Mergers have been accounted for as reorganizations of entities under common control as Mr. Elon Musk had a controlling financial interest in the Company, xAI and X through his majority voting interest in each such entity during the periods presented in these consolidated financial statements. The Company\'s consolidated financial statements have been prepared to reflect the retrospective combination of the net assets of the entities at their historical carrying amounts for all periods presented. **No new goodwill or other intangible assets have been recorded** and all historical related party transactions between the entities have been eliminated in consolidation."\n\nThe **implicit reasoning** (though not spelled out in the filing) is that under common-control accounting (ASC 805-50), the receiving entity records the transferred net assets at the transferor\'s historical carrying amounts rather than at fair value. Because no step-up to fair value occurs, no purchase-price premium is recognized and therefore no goodwill arises. The filing states this as a factual outcome of the accounting treatment without further elaboration.\n\n## 4. Historical Cost Basis of xAI\'s AI Technology or X\'s Platform Assets\n\n**There is no specific discussion** in the provided text of what the historical cost basis of xAI\'s AI technology (e.g., Grok, training infrastructure, models) or X\'s platform assets (e.g., user data, advertising systems, brand) represents. The filing only refers generically to "net assets of the entities at their historical carrying amounts" without any breakdown of the underlying asset categories, their nature, or what costs were historically capitalized. The only contextual detail provided is the operational history:\n\n- **X.AI Corp.** "began operations in March 